5: A little girl? No, I haven't seen one.
8:
Is that so... Well, if you do happen to
cross paths, could you look after her?
10:
We tried calling out to her, but she
ran off. Poor thing's hopelessly lost in
here.
14: Got it. We'll keep an eye out for her.
19:
*pant*
You really are... persistent little
monsters... aren't you!
22:
It's no use... At this rate, I'll run out of
magic...
39:
Phew. Looks like we made it just in
time.
44:
Um... Thank you for helping me out
when I was in trouble.
48:
If you don't mind, I'll be leaving now.
Bye-bye.
60:
We'd heard that a little girl was
wandering the Kaleidoscope alone.
Is that you?
64:
Wh-what! And who are you, exactly?
I was taught to never talk to
suspicious strangers. Are you some
sort of creeps?!
68:
Huh? No! We just want to help, that's
all—
73:
Those ears of yours. Are you
perchance an elf?
77:
Oh. I guess that makes her a drifter,
doesn't it.
82:
A drifter? That sounds even more
suspicious!
87:
It is only natural to be cautious, but
we mean you no harm. Allow us to
explain the circumstances.
91:
I mean... I guess I could hear you
out...
96:
This is a... different world?! No way, I
don't believe it!
100:
I'm afraid it is. You said your name
was Kyoka, right? Where are you
from?
109:
Landosol? Wait, isn't that the same
place the Gourmet Guild group is
from?
113: You know Pecorine and the others?!
117:
Yeah. They also ended up in this
world.
121:
I see... And come to think of it, it has
been a while since I last saw Mr.
Suspicious Creepy Guy...
135:
Regardless, I understand you may
be reluctant to believe us. Being
swept away to a faraway world
does sound like a tall tale.
137:
But the fact remains that this place
is very dangerous.
140:
For your sake, it would be best if you
came with us.
148:
But if you try any funny stuff, I'll ring
my Siren Amulet right away!
153:
N-no need for that. There'll be no
funny stuff. Promise.
157:
Er, you probably shouldn't walk so
far away from us. You might get lost
again.
165:
My mom and teachers all taught
me to be careful around strangers!
172: Well... I suppose it pays to be vigilant.
176:
Yeah. There are plenty of dangerous
people in the world. I can't blame
someone for being cautious.
180:
It would certainly explain why she
ran away from every adventurer
that tried to speak to her.
187:
Kyoka! Be careful, there are
monsters—
200:
Ouch... I think a part of your blast
scraped me.
204:
Oh no... I'm so sorry! You were doing
your best to protect me, but I—
210:
No, it's okay. Don't worry about it! It's
barely a scratch.
213:
Besides, your magic seriously
helped us out there. Without you, we
would have been in trouble.
218:
Indeed. For a child of your age, your
aptitude with magic is incredible!
226:
But please don't treat me like a kid!
I'm perfectly capable of fighting on
my own!
230:
That you are. Keep watching our
backs going forward, okay?
234: Yeah! You can count on me!
238:
Mr. Suspicious Creepy Guy! And
Kokkoro too!
242:
So that's the "creep" she was
referring to.
246:
Yeah... I'm sure it's just a friendly
inside joke or something. They look
like they're having fun.
251:
Yes. We should be safe to leave
Kyoka in their hands.
255:
Um... Mister Alk, Mister Light! I wanted
to say thank you.
259:
That and, I'm sorry... for thinking you
were suspicious.
264:
Don't sweat it. We're just happy we
got you out of the Kaleidoscope safe
and sound.
268:
I, uh, spoke with Kokkoro and she
says they don't know how to get
back to Landosol either.
277:
We are working hard to find a way
back home, and we have the
cooperation of Alk and his friends as
well.
282:
In that case... Please let me help you
too!
287:
Understood. Welcome to Starview
Village, Kyoka.
292: Okay! I'll do my absolute best!
